root: ^Jupiter is the fifth planet from the Sun and the largest in the Solar System.
^It is a gas giant with a mass more than two and a half times that of all the other planets
^in the Solar System combined, while being slightly less than one-thousandth the mass of the Sun.
^Jupiter is the third brightest natural object in the Earth's night sky after the Moon and Venus,
^and it has been observed since prehistoric times.
^It was named after Jupiter, the chief deity of ancient Roman religion.
^Did you know Jupiter is saving the Earth?
^Jupiter has been called the vacuum cleaner of the solar system
^because its gravity sucks in asteroids and comets, protecting us from those objects.
^Now let's protect it to some asteroid.
